John Alechenu, Abuja The Senate President Ahmed Lawan, the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila and the governors of Yobe, Kogi and Gombe are expected to converge on Abuja, on 18th December 2020, to discuss internal party democracy. The party leaders are expected to speak at the 2020 edition of the All Progressive Congress Press annual conference with the theme: “Contestation, a veritable process in deepening democratic norms, values and culture: The APC story.” This was contained in a statement titled, ‘APC: Lawan, govs, ministers, others to discuss internal contestation at Journalists’ conference,” signed by the Chairman Conference Planning Committee, Babatunde Ayeni, in Abuja, on Wednesday. Lawan is expected to give a keynote address while the Deputy Speaker will be giving insights into efforts being made by the National Assembly in the ongoing constitutional review. The statement read in part, “The governors expected at the 2020 conference include: the Chairman, Caretaker/Extra-Ordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC), Governor Mai Mala Buni of Yobe State, Governor Yahaya Bello of Kogi State and Governor Abubakar Mohammed Inuwa of Gombe State.” Copyright PUNCH.
